&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why binary search on the smaller array?&lt;/strong&gt; (Ensures &lt;code&gt;j &amp;gt;= 0&lt;/code&gt; always, preventing negative partition index.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What if arrays are equal length?&lt;/strong&gt; (Works the same — just processes both arrays equally.)&lt;/li&gt;
